The executive chairman, Abuja Municipal Area Council, Hon. Abdullahi Adamu Candido has announced the closure of all markets within the council with effect from Sunday 29th March, 2020 in order to curb the spread of Covid-19. The markets are those directly under the supervision of the Area Council. The chairman has also directed the Department of Environment in the council to immediately fumigate the market. The markets to be fumigated include Utako, FHA Lugbe, Relocation market Lugbe, Gwagwa, Nyanya, Aco mini, Jabi Park, Gwarinpa, Kugbo furniture, Kugbo spare part, Karshi, Karu andApo fish market respectively. He also urged all traders in the markets to cooperate with the authority and “abide by the directives for their safety and that of the entire residents.” “All traders and residents are to note that these markets remain closed till further directives and enjoined everyone to stay safe at this trying period,” he added.